sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
Executes 'Run Workday Service' subflow asynchronously.

Inputs:

  • Department - Retrieves the department data from Workday.
  • Location - Retrieves the location data from Workday.
  • Job Profile - Retrieves the job profile data from Workday.
  • Worker Profile - Retrieves the worker profile data from Workday.
  • Effective Worker Profile - Retrieves the Effective Worker Profiles data from Workday.
  • Future Worker Profile - Retrieves the Future Worker Profiles data from Workday.
  • Employment Data - Retrieves the Employment Data from Workday.
  • Retrieve All Data - Retrieves entire data for the selected entities.

Outputs:

  • Status - If the request is executed successfully, Status is set to “Success”. If there is a failure, Status is set to “Error”.
  • Error Message - Reason for error. Populated only when an error occurs.

Error Messages :

  • Encountered an error. Check log for more details

To use this action, Workday Spoke must be installed and corresponding Workday Connection and Credential must be created.
sys_hub_action_type_definition.name: Call Run Workday Service Subflow
